      section#story.content.story name="story"

        h2#story.story-title
          | The story of
          br
          | Cat Math Do
        .story-wrapper
          p When Oscar was 4 years old, I started teaching him the alphabet and counting to Ten. One day it occured to me that Oscar didn't know the difference between numbers and letters. So, I set out to introduce Oscar to their differences. I told him that Math is how numbers play together.
          p Then, I told him that the math playground has five rides;  plus, minus, times, divide, and equals. I then said that plus goes up and minus goes down.
          p It wasn't long after that I came up with the board game you're holding. We played it for over a year before I thought I should try to see if other kids would enjoy playing as much. I hope you do! :-)
          h2 A personal note from Dave
          p
            | (This part is not about Cat Math Do.)

          p Cat Math Do is my 5th business attempt. I invented, designed, coded, and marketing it in my free time. This game is an example of the new economy. We live in a day and age of amazing tools to work the way you want. Email me if you need help with developing your own dream and I'll do what I can to share what I've learned along the way.
